AKURE –  A chieftain of the All progressives Congress (APC) in Ondo State, Hon Akintoye Albert has called on the people of the state to support Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu in his drive to ensure security of life and property in the state. He noted that the support and cooperation of all security agencies in the state with the governor would help in sustaining the existing peace in the state. This was contained in his New Year message to the people of Irele and Okitipupa local governments and the state in general. Delta Monarch Commends Okowa, Offers Scholarship To 48 Students 2023 Governorship Race: Enugu East Insists On Ticket He urged  the new state Commissioner of Police, Oyediran Oyeyemi to make good his promise to make the state remain a safe and peaceful. Akintoye, a former member of House of Representatives, commended Governor Akeredolu’s efforts most especially in the area of ensuring security of life and property. He said: “Governor Akeredolu has shown exemplary leadership worthy of emulation among neighbouring states. Ondo is the most peaceful state in Nigeria and it is due to the way and manner the governor took the safety of his people as top priority.” Hon Akintoye, who is aspiring to represent his federal constituency in 2023 again, enjoined indigenes of the state both within the country and in the diaspora to come and invest in the state. According to him, “I urge all sons and daughters of Ondo State abroad to come home and invest because the state is safe and the governor is providing enabling environment for investments to thrive. POLL “Our airport is now very busy as people are coming in droves to invest in Ondo state.” He, therefore, promised his unflinching support for the present administration in efforts to build the state.